releases.changelog:
Built for pre-release. This dll will be updated with fixes and changes from https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/pull/24. Several mods will require being recompiled and may crash your game in the meantime. Additionally includes some extras from https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/pull/27

Tested working with `Beta 2025.7.16.446`

## New Features
* Added ToString() override for config keys
* Added Debug log at start of ExecutionHook

## Tweaks
* Fixes for Type update to FrooxEngine by @BlueCyro in https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/pull/12
  - Reworks the compatibility hash as now they are made per loaded DataModelAssembly
* Updated harmony to 2.3.3
  - Includes several improvements to targeting 
* Added harmony 2.3.5 as `0Harmony-Net9.dll`
  - Specifically for the Net9 Headless
* Removed Unsafe, HideModTypes, and HideLateTypes modloader config options as the type update should cover most to all of the use-cases for these
* Removed obsolete configuration handling option

## Additional notes
* Some additional testing and cleanup is planned for the hiding of types related patches and configs

If you want to run ResoniteModLoader on the new .Net 9 headless build, you will need to use the `0Harmony-Net9.dll` file instead of `0Harmony.dll`.

## New features
* Added headless property available to mods with `Modloader.IsHeadless` in #4 by @RileyGuy 
* Added several additional Debug log messages for debugging the modloader itself
  - Includes listing launch args in logs

## Tweaks
* Refactored out `LoadedResoniteMod` in #8 resolving #7 by @art0007i
* Fixed hash computation when other plugins are present fixing #3 
* Fixed NullReferenceException on startup caused by `IsValidGenericType` being refactored to a new class #5
* Applied .Net recommended performance and visibility suggestions 
* Removed unused 'nolibraries' config

## Additional notes
* Several small improvements in comment clarity
* Cleaned up csproj to use more Sdk defaults instead of redefining them
* Started moving docs over to a [Github Wiki](https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/wiki/)
  - Should improve linking to and finding of pages in the documentation

## Tweaks
 - Fixed headless unable to load files used for the loading indicator #2

## New features
* New OnChanged event for ModConfigurationKey's
`ExampleConfigKey.OnChanged += (value) => { Msg($"Key set to {value}"); };`
* Loading progress indicator on the splash screen to show the current status #1
  - Only shows modloader specific engine steps
  - Can be hidden with the `hidevisuals` [Modloader config](https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/blob/main/doc/modloader_config.md) option

## Tweaks
* TargetFramework is now net472
* Removed the headless build condition
  - A separate headless build is not currently needed
* Changed harmony id to `com.resonitemodloader.ResoniteModLoader`

## Additional notes
* Marked IncompatibleConfigurationHandlingOption.FORCE_LOAD as obsolete, use FORCELOAD
* Added xml doc to release

## Known issues
#2 On headless, you'll need to set the `hidevisuals` config

## Initial public release of the ResoniteModLoader
* Updated to use LangVersion C# 10
  - Mainly for GlobalDirectives and File Scoped Namespaces
* Removed deprecated and obsolete methods
* Added some additional logging and error handling around config usage and loading
* Mod configs should now be formatted with indentation instead of long single line
* Updated docs are in progress

## Additional notes
* Headless specific build may not be needed as `Newtonsoft.Json` has been updated and now matches on the client and headless

releases.changelog:
**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/hazre/VRCFTReceiver/compare/v1.0.3...v2.0.0-rc.1

## What's Changed
* Massive Rewrite of the code base.
* Added Native Eye (#2) and Face tracking support (AvatarExpressionDriver and EyeLinearDriver components)
* Removed ValueStreams and the need for manual setup and using the prefab.
*  Added OSCQuery support (VRCFaceTracking 5.2.3 now supported!) (#5)

## Usage
With OSCQuery being added, this mod now requires two different dependencies. 

- Download and move `vrc-oscquery-lib.dll` and `MeaMod.DNS.dll` to `rml_libs` folder, you find it where resonite is installed.
- Download and move `VRCFTReceiver.dll` to `rml_mods` folder.
- Install [VRCFaceTracking v5.2.3](https://github.com/benaclejames/VRCFaceTracking/releases/tag/5.2.3.0) if you don't have it already.
- Open VRCFT (with your preferred module installed) and Resonite and it should just work. In case, it doesn't try changing receiving port in the mod and the sending port on VRCFT (for example 9003)

This is a release candidate, if you find any issues or want to give feedback, either use [this thread](https://canary.discord.com/channels/901126079857692714/1267910572880429068) in [FrooxEngine Modding Discord](https://discord.gg/vCDJK9xyvm) or [open a issue](https://github.com/hazre/VRCFTReceiver/issues/new).

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/hazre/VRCFTReceiver/compare/v1.0.3...v1.0.4

- This is just a re-release of v1.0.3 with just some small string changes, so it can submited to [Resonite's mod manifest](https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/resonite-mod-manifest)

## What's Changed
* Fixed Face Tracking not working on initial load of a world.
* `vrc_parameters.json` template with all the parameters now gets created at `C:\Users\{USER}\AppData\LocalLow\VRChat\VRChat\OSC\vrcft\Avatars` on initial mod install, so you don't need to copy it over manually anymore. You can edit this file if you wish to change the parameters.

I recommend old users to delete their old  `vrc_parameters.json` file at `C:\Users\{USER}\AppData\LocalLow\VRChat\VRChat\OSC\{USER_UUID}\Avatars` directory, so the new file can be created automatically instead.

## What's Changed
* [Fixed ModConfigurationKeys having spaces and added IP selection.](https://github.com/hazre/VRCFTReceiver/commit/ee46de650ad6e1a3a261151e38f9e44d55127fe0)

> [!WARNING]
> Since the ModConfigurationKeys have changed, your mod configuration will reset.


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/hazre/VRCFTReceiver/compare/v1.0.1...v1.0.2

## What's Changed
* Implemented mod settings + fixed threading. by @knackrack615 in https://github.com/hazre/VRCFTReceiver/pull/1

## New Contributors

releases.changelog:
## Changes
- Corrected manual FOV config input to max at 180 degrees instead of 100
- Added limits to certain config options to prevent negative values
## Fixes
- Updated Desktop FOV setting check to be compatible with new settings
  - This also allows for FOV values to update in realtime when changing the Desktop FOV setting

## Hotfix
- Patches now no longer apply when using an outdated mod loader version (Issue discovered with help from @ItsAlphaNeon)

## Changes
- Reworked entire config page
- Reworked FOV setting to be automatic unless overriden
- Reworked scale compensation to be a single option
- Headless check now uses built in RML Headless check
- Changed some math operations to run faster
- User count is now uses total users instead of active users

## Fixes
- Fixed error when scale compensation was being applied to IK without an active user
- Corrected mistake in FOV math

## New Features
- Added culling based on end user inactivity, which includes the following:
  - Being unfocused from the game window in screen mode
  - Having the SteamVR/Oculus dashboard open while in VR

## Changes
- IK Update Falloff setting is now a 0% to 100% threshold relative to the Max Range setting
  - This lets you choose when updates begin reducing, the steps and curve are not configurable

## Changes
- Replaced the half rate updates option with an update rate enum including the following options:
  - Full
  - Half
  - Quarter
  - Eighth

**Requires [ResoniteModLoader 2.5.0](<https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/releases>) or later**

## Changes
- Updated some calculations that were running per frame to only run when needed

**Requires [ResoniteModLoader 2.5.0](<https://github.com/resonite-modding-group/ResoniteModLoader/releases>) or later**

## Changes
- Removed redundant behavior

## New Features
- Added option to make IK update slower as it approaches max range defined in config
- Added option to cut IK update rate in half

## Fixes
- Fixed IK without a user becoming active when grabbed

*Huge thanks to @LeCloutPanda for solution to handling IK update frequency*

## Changes
- Config option descriptions reworded for clarity
- FOV option is now a slider
- FOV option now takes 0 to 360 degrees as an input instead of -1 to 1

## Fixes
- Reduced lag when spawning the fullbody calibrator
- Made IK being enabled on the fullbody calibrator more reliable (solution by @LeCloutPanda)

## Changes
- Removed config auto updating
- Improved the flow of the culling checks to ideally do less work
- Replaced older method for the fullbody calibrator to only update when using the calibrator
- Improved behavior of the `MinUserCount` setting to only count active users
